    {
      "type": "Feature",
      "id": "lit-meera-bai-mewar",
      "geometry": {
        "type": "Point",
        "coordinates": [
          73.687,
          24.575
        ]
      },
      "properties": {
        "name": "Meera Bai — Bhakti Poetry of Mewar",
        "type": "literary_figure",
        "category": "custom",
        "district": "Mewar (Chittor)",
        "genre": "Bhakti poetry (Rajasthani-Braj)",
        "notes": {
          "facts": [
            "Sisodia princess of Mewar and Bhakti poet — her Krishna padas travel in every north-Indian devotional collection.",
            "Wrote in Rajasthani-Marwari-Braj mix; her \"Meera Padavali\" is compiled from oral tradition rather than a single manuscript.",
            "The Meera Temple at Chittorgarh Fort (Sisodia era) memorialises her — she is the only Rajputana Bhakti poet with a dedicated fort shrine."
          ],
          "significance": "high"
        },
        "state": "Rajasthan",
        "source": "Rajasthan Adhyan Class 12 Ch 9 (Literary Rajasthan)",
